<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id7a016855-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5" identifier="/us/usc/t16/s5723"><num value="5723">§ 5723.</num><heading> Exemption</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Chapter 10 of title 5 shall not apply to the Panel or to an advisory committee established under <ref href="/us/usc/t16/s5722">section 5722 of this title</ref>.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id7a016856-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5">(<ref href="/us/pl/106/450/tII/s204">Pub. L. 106–450, title II, § 204</ref>, <date date="2000-11-07">Nov. 7, 2000</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/114/1943">114 Stat. 1943</ref>; <ref href="/us/pl/117/286/s4/a/127">Pub. L. 117–286, § 4(a)(127)</ref>, <date date="2022-12-27">Dec. 27, 2022</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/136/4319">136 Stat. 4319</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="id7a016857-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="editorialNotes" id="id7a016858-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5"><heading class="centered"><b>Editorial Notes</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="amendments" id="id7a016859-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Amendments</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">2022—<ref href="/us/pl/117/286">Pub. L. 117–286</ref> substituted “Chapter 10 of title 5” for “The Federal Advisory Committee Act (5 U.S.C. App.)”.</p>
</note>
